# PROBER_DAEMON_MODE=on is the boot-contract opt-in this scenario exists to
# exercise. It inverts prober_check_conf's daemon gate (demanding `daemon on;`
# plus a pidfile at $PROBER_PREFIX/nginx.pid) and switches prober_boot/prober_stop
# from tracking the master by $! to tracking it by that pidfile. A USR2 binary
# upgrade cannot be delivered to a foregrounded (daemon off) master -- see the
# nginx.conf header -- so without this the scenario could not run at all.
#
# Sourced per-scenario in a run-scenario.sh subprocess, so the opt-in cannot
# leak into any other scenario's boot.
PROBER_DAEMON_MODE=on
